There's been a land invasion in Tembisa in the East Rand. The Red Ants are there removing the structures. JOHANNESBURG - The Red Ant Security Relocation and Eviction Services were deployed to Tembisa in the East Rand where people were constructing dwellings on Tuesday. READ: Cape Town hit hard by land invasions People who went to the open field and began erecting dwellings said they had been told by political representatives that they were allowed to build there. Later the Red Ants arrived and burned the structures. The residents asked that politicians not use them as pawns but said they also have nowhere else to go.